Yesterday I drove by a billboard that said to drink Red Bull after work when you are tired so you can go to the gym instead of straight to bed. Caffeine is a drug that is widely promoted in our culture yet you can't advertise (or in some places even posses) a plant that is non-toxic and impossible to overdose on..? Some people are serving longer sentences for smoking cannabis then pedophilia.
-
Then I see on social media that a child died from a caffeine overdose drinking McDonalds soda, an energy drink, and Mountain Dew. If this doesn't open your eyes to something is seriously wrong with this planet I don't know what will.
-
If nature is illegal, freedom doesn't exist. No one has the right to deny a person access to plants that grow naturally on the Earth. It is our divine right to freely explore our own consciousness. My highest calling is to legalize nature and provide access to these sacred medicines to everyone. Respect to the conscious soldiers fighting in this war for freedom alongside me. #salute #highercalling
-
"Psychedelics are illegal not because a loving government is concerned that you may jump out of a third story window. Psychedelics are illegal because they dissolve opinion structures and culturally laid down models of behaviour and information processing. They open you up to the possibility that everything you know is wrong." -Terrence McKenna

The "Cool Walk" and "Cool Skip" is one one of the 6 ESSENTIAL dribbles needed for effective guard play. "Ball turning," not carrying, is one of the 14 #Ball #Control Principles needed to develop into a #monster handler! The Cool Walk/Skip is THE most important dribble concept that can be taught.

The "Cool Walk/Skip" allows for you to:

1. Control Pace and defender (won't be sped up) without body contact unless #neccessary
2. Handle Pressure/Protect the Ball
3. Transition seamlessly into protection breakdowns or faceup atttacks
4. Patiently wait for plays
*5. Conserve energy
6. Flow 
7. Offset defensive quickness and size in most instances
